rComments: This is the best prof ever, explains the course clearly and was definitely understandable, makes some jokes during class times and as long as You follow the rules, he is always lenient on things and is very caring too!

He is super hilarious and very passionate during labs. He definitely makes me look forward to lab time. Straightforward, friendly, and open to any comments. Sometimes off track but will get back on track knowing we all have labs to be completed by the end of classes. Make sure to take notes of his presentations.

Dr Jeff is an amazing guy to have in lab. He is always very detailed in his descriptions so when he gives you the objective of the lab be sure to jot it down bc it will most likely be on the on test. rComments: He's a great, down-to-earth, relate-able prof with interesting labs that keep students interested. Granted, the lecture part may drag on a bit too long, and occasionally cuts into time to complete the lab, the labs make it worthwhile.
Awesome human being!
Cool guy, interesting lessons. Labs sometimes are just boring and useless but other times, they're pretty cool. Lab tests were okay, if you take notes during labs.

Sniffy the virtual rat was just not necessary. I did not learn that much about training a mouse. I think he means well but I just was not interested in the study. If you do badly in his lab test your psychology mark will drop in psy100 even if you have done well in Dax's tests.
Nicest professor ever. Very approachable and extremely helpful. He makes you want to be his buddy. His labs are really interesting and I'd go to them even if they weren't mandatory.
